CO2 Emissions by Country

The CO2 emission from China and United States are substantially higher than any other country

US Income Equality over Time

The top 10% percentage of population share a higher percentage of total wealth, denoting that most earning in the US goes to a fewer number of people

Health Expenditures by Country

United States health care expenditure is the highest, denoting that its expensive in US for health care

Changes in Forestation around the World

Both China and US are planting more trees to improve the environment

Rural and Urban population in China and United States

This visualization compares the trend between rural and urban population in China and United States

Chinas urban population has increased rapidly since 1980s, while USs urban population grown steadily

Comparing two countries side by side will contrast the rural and urban population trend over the time

This visualization is effective, as using lines (instead of point) will denote the tendency of population change (increase steadily or increase sharply)
